cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper is about pedestrian detection using multispectral images and convolutional neural networks. The primary focus is on improving the detection performance under challenging illumination conditions. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses different network architectures and their adaptations, which suggests that machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) are also relevant sub-categories. The proposed method is designed for robotics applications, which makes robotics (cs.RO) another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper uses multispectral images, which can be considered as a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM).
